# dz-dashboard — example crontab (Phase 2)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# The dashboard is read-only: it has no pipeline to schedule (that's Phase 1's
# cron). The only operational need is keep-alive — start it on reboot. This is
# the simpler ALTERNATIVE to the systemd user service in
# scripts/dz-dashboard.service; use one or the other, not both.
#
# Prefer the systemd unit if available — it restarts on crash, not just on
# reboot, and gives you `journalctl` logs. Use this cron entry on boxes without
# a usable user systemd.
#
# Install:
#   crontab -l | cat - scripts/cron.example | crontab -   # append to current crontab
#
# Before installing, replace the placeholders:
#   <PROJECT_ROOT>  absolute path to this checkout       (e.g. /home/you/dz-dashboard)
#   <DZ_DASHBOARD>  absolute path to the dz-dashboard entrypoint
#                   (`command -v dz-dashboard`, or
#                    <PROJECT_ROOT>/.venv/bin/dz-dashboard for a uv-managed venv).
#
# Build the SPA once before relying on this (the entry serves web/dist):
#   make build-web
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

SHELL=/bin/bash
PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin
PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1

# On reboot — start the dashboard (BFF + built SPA, single-origin on :8800).
# `setsid` detaches it from cron so it keeps running; logs go to data/logs.
@reboot  cd <PROJECT_ROOT> && mkdir -p data/logs && DASHBOARD_STATIC_DIR=<PROJECT_ROOT>/web/dist setsid <DZ_DASHBOARD> serve >> data/logs/dashboard.log 2>&1
